author: cbs8
title: Single vehicle crash near Carthage leads to one death
text: CARTHAGE, MISSOURI - A 18 year old man was killed in a single vehicle crash 2.5 miles north of Carthage. The accident occurred at 7 PM last night (October 7th). According to the Missouri Highway Patrol, Weston M. Greenstreet, of Oronogo, MO, was driving his vehicle soutbound on County Road 180. Greenstreet's vehicle lost control, traveled off the roadway, overturned several times, and struck two more trees. Greenstreet was pronounced dead at the scene. MHP did confirm that Greenstreet was wearing a safety restraint.
